==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cutworm
<hw>Cut"worm`</hw> <pr>(-w?rm`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A caterpillar which at night eats off young plants of cabbage,
corn, etc., usually at the ground. Some kinds ascend fruit trees and eat
off the flower buds. During the day, they conceal themselves in the
earth. The common cutworms are the larv⟦ae⟧ of various species of
<gen>Agrotis</gen> and related genera of noctuid moths.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cuvette</ent>⟦br⟧
